<br>What’s extremely different?
<p>Examples of what we know that are now different
Combined the str and unicode into a separate structure byte. Str and Unicode were extremely similar, ‘Hi’ vs u’Hi’, there was no real difference between those two besides how they were made; str were created by the program, while unicode, though it can be created, generally came from an outside source, like a website.
Give an example of this
</p>  

